Market Challenges
High Initial Capital Expenditure
Implementing linerless printing equipment often necessitates substantial upfront investment in specialized rollers, clip‑control software, and precision ink delivery units. For small‑to‑mid‑size label manufacturers, these costs can act as a barrier to entry and slow the overall market penetration.
Skill Gap in Workforce
Transitioning from traditional linered to linerless processes requires operators to master new maintenance protocols and media handling techniques. Organizations must develop training programs, which can delay early deployment timelines.
Compatibility with Existing Production Lines
Legacy print lines engineered for linered rolls may not accommodate linerless media without significant retrofitting. The need for re‑tooling can discourage operators from shifting away from the established technology.
